Description: Fix CVE-2026-54513 — validate array component types in BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator
 BasicPolymorphicTypeValidator.Builder.allowIfSubTypeIsArray() previously
 approved any array type via clazz.isArray() without checking the element
 type against the configured sub-class allow-list. An attacker could bypass
 an explicit allow-list by wrapping a denied class as an array (e.g.
 Evil[]), causing plain bean deserialization of the component with no
 further PTV invocation (CWE-184 / CWE-502).
 .
 Backport of upstream commit 24529da29fdf46ff94ca38de9ebf31cd188f5e8e
 (GH-5983 / databind#5981) to jackson-databind 3.1.1. Test additions from
 the upstream commit are omitted (build skips tests).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/commit/24529da29fdf46ff94ca38de9ebf31cd188f5e8e
Bug: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/issues/5981
Last-Update: 2026-07-07

